The heat of charity is poor indeed where not God alone, but foreign things
besides and with God. urge and excite us towards the works of virtue. Such
men are fickle of heartï¼š for in all the things which they do, nature is
secretly seeking its own, often without their knowledge, for they know not
themselves.
